        <div class="hero-body">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="title">
                    Spotifier's Privacy Policy
                </h1>
                <h2 class="subtitle">
                    Information on how Spotifier collects your data
                </h2>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container is-fluid">

        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="title">Data Collection</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">By using this service, Spotifier needs to collect some data for it to work.
                The data collected are
                your:
            </p>

            <ol>
                <li>Spotify's username and display name (It's not your email)</li>
                <li>Spotify's user id (A random identifier string which is tied to your Spotify account)</li>
                <li>Spotify's liked songs (50 of the latest liked songs)</li>
                <li>Spotify's profile picture(s)</li>
            </ol>

        </section>


        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="title">How does Spotifier process my data?</h2>
            <p>When you use our service, Spotifier automatically creates a user profile based on your
                name, id and liked
                songs! The name is used to display when you visit the user page while the id is used so that there is no
                duplicates of spotify accounts on the server and the liked songs is used to display to the public.</p>
        </section>
    </div>

